reviews.text: Nice place to escape the heat and crowds.very nice selection and different from what the offer in the States. They even have a coffee bar though I did not try. Do not know if they use real alcohol or just load it up with caffeine to give you that lovely feeling. For myself, I just got something normal and just kicked it in their spacious area. Pretty nice.

A large & lively yet quiet Café infused with gorgeous hipster music & ever friendly staff. Lighting that transitions between cozy & bright suiting your every need from unwinding to working. A well flavored experience for all.

Located in basement one of Gala Palace, this Starbuck outlet is easily accessible via an escalator from Dundas Street. With 4,500 square feet of floor space, there are ample seats available here. Interestingly, there is also daily coffee tasting available at this particular outlet as well.
Pretty nice peaceful place in the morning for a cuppa. Staff could be bit more well trained and smile more.

I ordered just a black coffee, a chai & a ham & cheese croissant. The croissant arrived first then the coffee but not the chai. I waited 20 min and then asked if it was coming and they said yes. 20 min more and still nothing, the food got cold in the meantime, I went to ask again and they replied it was coming still nothing until my husband went to ask again and they realised they were keeping forgetting about it. It wasn't a particularly busy day either.

reviews.text: Big one n depending you like it or not, the HnM Brand
Went to the government offices on the 12th floor.  Staff was helpful and courteous.
This is one of the venues that you can get your new ID card processed. The Smart ID card center is on the 12/F. Parking facility is also available nearby.

A typical commercial building. There were many companies that set up their offices or sales stations here, e.g. eyewear companies, telecommunications companies. It was very crowded because there was a lot of people visiting. Moreover, you can find the Immigration Department on the 12th floor.
Visited the H&M there. Very spacious and it is just next to the famous Sai Yeung Choi South Street.
